<li id="cite_note-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The Sanskrit term <i>brahmavadini</i> means a female <i>brahmavadi</i>. According to <a href="/wiki/Monier_Monier-Williams" title="Monier Monier-Williams">Monier-Williams</a>'s <i>Sanskrit-English Dictionary</i>, <i>brahmavādín</i> means "discoursing on sacred texts, a defender or expounder of the <i>Veda</i>, one who asserts that all things are to be identified with <a href="/wiki/Brahman" title="Brahman">Brahman</a>". It does not mean "one who speaks like God".</span></li>
